6	//! Bounded families of ahead-of-time compiled kernel variants.
7	//!
8	//! A kernel family gives stable IDs to a small, fixed set of entries and keeps
9	//! selection policy outside the kernels themselves:
10	//!
11	//! ```text
12	//! Force(id) -> resolve + validate --------------------------> Override
13	//! Auto      -> eligible cache hit --------------------------> Cache
14	//!           -> selector(eligible variants) -> cache store --> Selector
15	//! ```
16	//!
17	//! The module is deliberately CPU-only. Callers decide which problem and
18	//! hardware facts matter, how to select among eligible variants, and whether
19	//! to keep an in-memory or persistent cache.
20	
21	use core::{convert::Infallible, fmt};
22	
23	use thiserror::Error;
24	
25	/// Stable namespace for a kernel family and its cache entries.
26	///
27	/// Bump `revision` when variant membership, eligibility, selector/preference
28	/// policy, tuning methodology, or the meaning of a variant ID changes. A
29	/// reorder also requires a bump unless selection and tuning are explicitly
30	/// order-independent: caches store stable IDs, but selectors receive eligible
31	/// variants in declaration order.
