227	/// Cache adapter for automatic family selection.
228	///
229	/// Implementations must include both `family.name()` and `family.revision()` in
230	/// their key. Cached IDs are treated as untrusted hints: unknown or newly
231	/// ineligible values fall back to the selector and are overwritten.
232	/// Best-effort persistent adapters can translate I/O failures into misses or
233	/// no-op stores; an error returned from this trait deliberately stops selection.
234	pub trait KernelSelectionCache<Problem, Id> {
235	    /// Cache backend failure. The thread-portable bound matches host
236	    /// worker/async selection use.
